# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# <BLANK LINE>
# <body>
# <BLANK LINE>
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# - feat (new feature)
# - fix (bug fix)
# - docs (changes to documentation)
# - style (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
# - refactor (refactoring production code)
# - test (adding missing tests, refactoring tests; no production code change)
# - chore (updating build tasks etc; no production code change)
# - perf (code change that improves performance)
# - ci (changes to CI configuration files and scripts)
# - build (changes that affect the build system or external dependencies)
# - revert (reverts a previous commit)

# Scope should be one of the following:
# - astro (changes to Astro configuration or components)
# - react (changes to React components)
# - tailwind (changes to Tailwind CSS configuration or styles)
# - content (changes to content, such as text or images)
# - deps (changes to dependencies)
# - config (changes to configuration files)
# - *

# The subject should use impertivite tone and say what you did.
# The body should go into more detail about changes made.
# The footer should contain issue references or breaking change notes.

# For example:
# feat(astro): add new blog post page
#
# - Created new Astro page for rendering blog posts
# - Integrated with Markdown content source
# - Added meta tags for SEO
#
# Resolves: #123
